speechtext:
Mr. Speaker, there have been consultations between the various House Leaders with respect to the business for tomorrow, at which time we are planning to have the economic statement. I have before me and want to present to the House for approval at this time, by unanimous consent, the following Order:
That, notwithstanding any Standing Order, on Thursday, November 8, 1984, at six o'clock p.m. the House shall suspend its sitting until 6:30 o'clock p.m., and, at that time the business to be considered shall be a statement by the Minister of Finance;
Provided that upon the conclusion of the statement the Minister may lay upon the Table certain Notices of Ways and Means Motions related thereto, and that after a reply to the statement from one Member of each of the other recognized Parties, the Speaker shall adjourn the House.
